Dependencies

 1. Install NuGet Command Line
    Download it from http://nuget.codeplex.com/releases
 2. Make a Packages directory
    $ mkdir Packages
 3. Download libraries using nuget
    $ nuget install Model/packages.config -o Packages
    $ nuget install WebApp/packages.config -o Packages
 4. Make a MVC 3 directory inside Packages
    $ mkdir Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0
 5. Copy MVC 3 dll files
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.Mvc.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.Helpers.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.Razor.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.WebPages.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.WebPages.Razor.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/
    $ cp <asp.net mvc 3 path>/System.Web.WebPages.Deployment.dll Packages/AspNetMVC.3.0.0.0/

Mono's StringLengthAttribute Fix

 1. Download the patched DataAnnotations assembly
    Download it from http://mictlanix.com/files/DataAnnotations-Patched.zip
 2. Replace in GAC (.Net 4 Profile)
    $ cp System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations.dll <mono path>/lib/mono/gac/System.ComponentModel.DataAnnotations/4.0.0.0__31bf3856ad364e35/
